      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In both transcripts, Candidate 1 and Candidate 2 convey a similar approach to handling a frustrated customer—listening, acknowledging frustration, and seeking a solution—though their methods of communication have slight differences. Candidate 1 is more formal in manner, correctly spelling \"without interrupting\" and showing the word \"so\" for coherence. Candidate 2 lacks some spelling and punctuation which may reflect poorly on their ability to communicate effectively in a professional office environment. While both candidates seem competent, Candidate 1 demonstrates a higher level of professional communication suitable for an interview.",
